        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-12T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-12T20:00:00-05:00" n="351" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d351">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894A.00/3–1347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-13T09:00:00+08:00">March 13, 1947—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 13—6:08 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>539. Col. Dau returned from Taipei (Embtel 500, Mar. 9) Mar. 11 and his view
                    situation telegraphed War Department with request information be transmitted to
                    State Department.<note n="19" xml:id="d351fn1">See telegram D 4080, <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Message from Taipei Mar. 11, 3 p.m. quotes reputable Formosan sources as stating
                    systematic repression has started with arrests and executions. Embassy has taken
                    steps indirectly to bring to attention Generalissimo substance information it
                    has received on repression.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
